{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} [[Image:Filmintypewriter.jpg|thumb|A sheet of correction paper in a typewriter.]] '''Correction paper''', or '''correction film''', its plastic based equivalent, is a tab of [[plastic]] with one side [[coated paper|coated]] with white correction material. It is used to correct [[typing error]]s made when using a [[typewriter]]. When inserted between the [[paper]] and the ribbon, the impression of the typebar presses the shape of the character into the film, which prints the white correction material onto the paper, hiding the erroneous [[Glyph|character]] and preparing the [[document]] for the correct character.
