{{Politics of Zambia}}
The '''Ministry of Energy''' is a [[Ministry (government department)|ministry]] in [[Zambia]]. It is headed by the Minister of Energy.
In 2012 the Ministry of Water and Energy was merged with the [[Ministry of Mines and Minerals Development|Ministry of Mines]] to form the Ministry of Mines Energy and Water Development. The merger was reversed in 2015, with the Ministry of Energy and Water Development coming into being.<ref>[https://www.daily-mail.co.zm/zambia-needs-well-defined-roles-ministries/ Zambia needs well-defined roles for ministries] Daily Mail, 19 September 2015</ref> In 2016 Water Development was transferred to the new [[Ministry of Water Development, Sanitation and Environmental Protection]].
